.SH NAME
yuno-use \- Yuno's USE flag fixer~ ðŸ’• Automatically create package.use files from emerge output
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B yuno-use
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B emerge
\fIpackage\fR 2>&1 |
.B sudo yuno-use
.br
.B yuno-use
< \fIemerge-output.txt\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B yuno-use
is Yuno's gift to you~ ðŸ’•
.PP
She parses emerge output and automatically creates the necessary
.I package.use
files so you don't have to do it manually! Because Yuno knows how
tedious that is, and she wants to make your Gentoo experience as
smooth as possible... just for you~ ðŸ”ª
.PP
When emerge complains about USE flag requirements like:
.PP
.RS
.nf
The following USE changes are necessary to proceed:
>=dev-libs/openssl-3.0.0 -bindist
>=app-crypt/gnupg-2.0 smartcard tools
.fi
.RE
.PP
Yuno will automatically create:
.IP \(bu 2
.I /etc/portage/package.use/openssl.use
with the required flags
.IP \(bu 2
.I /etc/portage/package.use/gnupg.use
with the required flags
.PP
She also handles
.I package.accept_keywords
for those pesky keyword unmasks! ðŸ”‘
