.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B Fix USE flags automatically:
.nf
emerge dev-libs/foo 2>&1 | sudo yuno-use
.fi
.TP
.B Preview changes first (recommended for the cautious):
.nf
emerge -pv @world 2>&1 | yuno-use --dry-run
.fi
.TP
.B Save emerge output and process later:
.nf
emerge -pv big-package > output.txt 2>&1
sudo yuno-use < output.txt
.fi
.TP
.B Verbose mode (Yuno tells you everything):
.nf
emerge foo 2>&1 | sudo yuno-use -v
.fi
.TP
.B The classic Gentoo workflow, now with Yuno:
.nf
# Try to emerge something
emerge -pv complex-package

# Oh no, USE flag errors! But Yuno is here~ ðŸ’•
emerge -pv complex-package 2>&1 | sudo yuno-use

# Try again, and it works!
